%Tutorial --------------------------  EDIT  ---------------------------
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
+
%                     -----------------------------------
                      ×       Edit Macro  "CONT"        ×
                      -----------------------------------
+
%FUNCTION  :+This Edit macro may be used to place a continuation charact
             column 72 of data line(s).
%SYNTAX :+   CONT
             CONT HELP or H
%USE :+      Type%CONT+on the COMMAND line and mark the range of continu
             with the "C" range command on the line numbers, as i.e. :
            %COMMAND ===> CONT
        ---> CC+500           MYMAC PARM1,
             000600             PARM2,
       %---> CC+700             PARM3,
             000800             LASTPARM
            %Result :+a%X+is placed in column 72 of lines numbered 500,
                      and 700. Identical process is obtained with :
       %---> C3+500           MYMAC PARM1,
)PROC
  &ZCONT = PAJTCONT
)END
